Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long pieces. Trim @scallions{2} whites and greens; cut whites into 1-inch pieces and thinly slice greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{2%ounce} (you'll use the rest later), and as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Set aside until ready to use.

Once water is boiling, add @Lo Mein Noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Drain and set aside.

While noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @tofu{1}, green beans, scallion whites, ginger, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Drain any excess grease from pan (or use a #paper towel{} and #tongs{} to sop it up!).

Add @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, remaining chili sauce, and @water{1/4%cup} to pan with tofu and green beans; continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is warmed through, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Remove from heat.

To pan with tofu and green beans, add drained noodles and @butter{1/2%tbsp}. Toss to combine; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide lo mein between #shallow bowls{}. Drizzle with as much firecracker sauce as you like. Top with scallion greens and serve.